    <prp:code/>
    <prp:abstract>MACS J0717.5+3745 is a massive merging cluster at redshift z=0.55. From recent high resolution (13") SZE imaging at 3mm using GBT/Mustang, it is seen that the SZE peak is offset from the local peak in X-ray surface brightness map (Mroczkowski et al. 2012). This phenomenon is characteristic of a cluster merger with a small impact parameter (~150kpc) and a very high imact velocity (&gt; 4000 km/s) (Molnar et al. 2012). The scenario, however, also predicts a secondary peak in SZE near the local X-ray peak. This secondary peak is lost to beam dilution with the 13" beam in the Mustang observation. Here we propose a single pointing of ALMA covering both the primary and secondary peaks in the expected SZE distribution with 4" resolution to recover this secondary peak and constrain the dynamical parameters.
</prp:abstract>
